                      'href=/subscribe>Subscribe</a></li></ul></div></div><div '
                      'class=hidden-phone><div class="moduletable span 3"><div '
                      'class="custom span 3"><div style="text-align: '
                      'right;"><a href=http://www.facebook.com/AtlanticCouncil '
                      'target=_blank><img '
                      'src=/images/Buttons/sidebar-facebook.png alt=sFacebook '
                      'width=50 height=50 class=icon /></a><a '
                      'href=http://www.twitter.com/AtlanticCouncil '
                      'target=_blank><img '
                      'src=/images/Buttons/sidebar-twitter.png alt=Twitter '
                      'class=icon /></a><a '
                      'href=https://instagram.com/atlanticcouncil/ '
                      'target=_blank><img '
                      'src=/images/Buttons/sidebar-insta.png alt=Instagram '
                      '/></a><img src=/images/Buttons/sidebar-youtube.png '
                      'alt=YouTube class=icon '
                      '/></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id=content '
                      'class="span6 "><div id=main><div '
                      'id=system-message-container> </div><div '
                      'class=item-page><div class=create> September 7, '
                      '2017\\t</div><div class=page-header><h1> Double Issue '
                      'Brief Launch: Consumers and Competition </h1><div '
                      'class=createdby> By Africa Center </div></div><div '
                      'class="addthis_toolbox top"> <a '
                      'class=addthis_button_email><img '
                      'src=/templates/acus/images/icon_email_gray.gif /></a> '
                      '<a '
                      'href="/events/past-events/double-issue-brief-launch-consumers-and-competition?tmpl=component&print=1" '
                      'title=Print class=modal rel="{handler: \\\'iframe\\\', '
                      'size: {x: 640, y: 480}}"><img '
                      'src=/templates/acus/images/icon_print_gray.gif /></a> '
                      '<a class=addthis_button_twitter><img '
                      'src=/templates/acus/images/icon_twitter_gray.gif /></a> '
                      '<a class=addthis_button_facebook><img '
                      'src=/templates/acus/images/icon_facebook_gray.gif '
                      '/></a> </div> <script '
                      'src="//s7.addthis.com/js/300/addthis_widget.js#pubid=ra-52a34d9b6b1b72b6"></script><div '
                      'class=item-image> <img class=caption title="Africa '
                      'Center Deputy Director Bronwyn Bruton speaks with '
                      'Senior Fellow Aubrey Hruby and Kupanda Capital '
                      'Co-Founder Linda Oramasionwu." '
                      'src=/images/acevents/AfricaCenter/2017/7J7A0013_FEAT.jpg '
                      'alt=""/> </div><div class=clearfix></div>On September '
                      '7, 2017, the Atlantic Council\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Africa '
                      'Center launched two new issue briefs that tackle the '
                      'complexities of investing in Africa. The first, titled '
                      '<a '
                      'href=/publications/issue-briefs/escaping-china-shadow><em>Escaping '
                      'China\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Shadow: Finding '
                      'America\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Competitive Edge in '
                      'Africa</em></a><em>,</em> was written by senior fellow '
                      '<strong>Aubrey Hruby</strong>, and the second, <a '
                      'href=/publications/issue-briefs/capturing-the-african-consumer-market><em>Capturing '
                      'the African Consumer Market: Truths, Trends, and '
                      'Strategies for the Road Ahead</em></a>, by '
                      '<strong>Aleksandra Gadzala</strong>. <br /> <br /> '
                      'Atlantic Council Vice President and Africa Center '
                      'Director Dr. <strong>J. Peter Pham</strong> welcomed '
                      'attendees, and Africa Center Director for Programs and '
                      'Studies and Deputy Director <strong>Bronwyn '
                      'Bruton</strong> set the stage for remarks by Hruby. <br '
                      '/><br /> In her remarks, Hruby argued that Chinese '
                      'dominance in African markets does not automatically '
                      'preclude US business successes on the continent. She '
                      'asserted that US companies should invest in sectors '
                      'where the United States has a competitive advantage, '
                      'such as professional and business services, finance, '
                      'and agribusiness. Additionally, the US government '
                      'should do more to encourage small- and medium-sized '
                      'enterprises to invest in Africa, namely through the '
                      'mobilization of the Department of Commerce and Small '
                      'Business Administration, larger investments in '
                      'institutions such as the Export-Import Bank and the '
                      'Overseas Private Investment Corporation, and movement '
                      'of US-Africa investment seminars outside of the '
                      'Washington, DC region. <br /><br /> In<em> Capturing '
                      'the African Consumer Market, </em>Gadzala argues that '
                      'the much-vaunted African '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cmiddle-class\\xe2\\x80\\x9d is truly a '
                      'bifurcated entity. While recent investments in Africa '
                      'cater to a wealthier upper segment, Gadzala warns that '
                      'there are many pitfalls in misjudging trends and '
                      'spending habits of a large, lower '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9centry-level consumer\\xe2\\x80\\x9d '
                      'segment involved in the informal sector. Investors in '
                      'Africa should factor this in to their calculus, as well '
                      'as consider the power of mobile technology and '
                      'specialized \\xe2\\x80\\x9csecondary '
                      'cities\\xe2\\x80\\x9d outside of national capitals and '
                      'metropolises.&nbsp; <br /><br /> <strong>Linda '
                      '</strong><strong>Oramasionwu</strong>, co-founder of '
                      'Kupanda Capital and veteran of the emerging and '
                      'frontier market spaces, joined Hruby in a discussion '
                      'moderated by Bruton. Oramasionwu spoke of the diverse '
                      'investment opportunities in Africa, highlighting '
                      'Nigeria\\xe2\\x80\\x99s film industry, which has '
                      'maintained impressive growth despite national economic '
                      'woes. Hruby and Oramasionwu also took questions from '
                      'the audience, which consisted of representatives from '
                      'the US and other government as well as the private '
                      'sector.<br /><br /><img '
                      'src=/images/logos/20151215_Diversifying_African_Trade_logos.jpg '
                      'alt="20151215 Diversifying African Trade logos" '
                      'width=500 height=86 class=noformat /><br /><em>These '
                      'issue briefs are part of a partnership between the '
                      'Atlantic Council\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Africa Center and the '
                      'OCP Policy Center and are made possible by generous '
                      'support from the OCP Foundation.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a '
                      'href=/publications/issue-briefs/escaping-china-shadow><em>Escaping '
                      'China\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Shadow: Finding '
                      'America\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Competitive Edge in Africa</em> '
                      'is available for download here.</a><br /><br /> <a '
                      'href=/publications/issue-briefs/capturing-the-african-consumer-market><em>Capturing '
                      'the African Consumer Market: Truths, Trends, and '
                      'Strategies for the Road Ahead</em> is available for '
                      'download here.</a></em> <ul class="tags inline"> <li '
                      'class="tag-53 tag-list0" itemprop=keywords> <a '
                      'href=/regions/africa class="label label-info"> Africa '
                      '</a> </li> <li class="tag-99 tag-list1" '
                      'itemprop=keywords> <a '
                      'href=/component/tags/tag/99-africa-center class="label '
                      'label-info"> Africa Center </a> </li> <li '
                      'class="tag-429 tag-list2" itemprop=keywords> <a '
                      'href=/people/aubrey-hruby class="label label-info"> '
                      'Aubrey Hruby </a> </li> </ul><div '
                      'class="addthis_toolbox bottom"><div class=scroll><a '
                      'href=#top><img '
                      'src=/templates/acus/images/icon_backtotop.gif '
                      '/></a></div> <a class=addthis_button_email><img '
                      'src=/templates/acus/images/icon_email_white.gif /></a> '
                      '<a '
                      'href="/events/past-events/double-issue-brief-launch-consumers-and-competition?tmpl=component&print=1" '

                 'GENSUIKYO’S CALLHelp Build the Peace Wave– September '
                 '20-26Dear Friends,As many of you will have seen, growing out '
                 'of the World Conference against A- & H- Bombs in Hiroshima '
                 'and Nagasaki, Gensuikyo has initiated a call for a global '
                 '“Peace Wave” beginning at noon on September 20, the day that '
                 'the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons will be '
                 'open for signatures at the United Nations. A number of our '
                 'European partner organizations have already signed '
                 'on.Gensuikyo’s call, which follows below, is for '
                 'decentralized activities consistent with the political '
                 'cultures of each country and the needs and methods or '
                 'organizations committed to nuclear weapons abolition.After '
                 'consultation, Peace and Planet encourages member '
                 'organizations and all others to help build the Peace Wave. '
                 'It is critical that as many of the 122 governments that '
                 'voted in favor of the Treaty in July now sign and ratify it. '
                 'We believe that the most important Ban Treaty campaigning '
                 'will likely be in NATO and Asia-Pacific “nuclear umbrella” '
                 'states. If just one or two governments break from their '
                 'nuclear masters, the foundations of the potentially '
                 'omnicidal nuclear disorder can be powerfully shaken.For '
                 'those of us in nuclear weapons states, the Peace Wave '
                 'provides an opportunity to educate our movements and '
                 'communities about the Prohibition Treaty and to build '
                 'support for other nuclear disarmament initiatives, from '
                 'challenging the billions being spent to upgrade nuclear '
                 'arsenals and their delivery systems, to preventing '
                 'catastrophic wars with North Korea and Iran.Let’s build the '
                 'Peace Wave!For Peace and Planet,Joseph GersonP.S. Please '
                 'send notice of Peace Wave events you have planned '
                 'to*protected email*GENSUIKYO’S CALLLet Us Launch the “Peace '
                 'Wave” Actions from September 20 to 26, calling on all '
                 'governments of the World to Join the Treaty to Prohibit '
                 'Nuclear WeaponsOn the occasion of the 72nd anniversary of '
                 'the atomic bombing of Hiroshima and Nagasaki, the 2017 World '
                 'Conference against A and H Bombs called on the peoples of '
                 'the world to launch international join international '
                 'simultaneous actions “Peace Wave” to urge all national '
                 'governments to join the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear '
                 'Weapons from September 20, the day when the Treaty will be '
                 'open for signatures, until 26, the International Day for the '
                 'Total Elimination of Nuclear Weapons.The Treaty on the '
                 'Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons was adopted on July 7this '
                 'year with the support of 122 States. It is a groundbreaking '
                 'treaty to open a path to achieve the total elimination of '
                 'nuclear weapons, which has long been aspired by the '
                 'Hibakusha and the peoples of the entire world. Declaring '
                 'that nuclear weapons are inhumane weapons in violation of '
                 'international law, international humanitarian law and '
                 'international human rights law, the treaty prohibits the '
                 'development, production, tests, manufacturing, acquisition, '
                 'possession, stockpiling, use and threat of use of nuclear '
                 'weapons.Among the 193 member states of the United Nations, '
                 'only 9 countries are in possession of nuclear weapons. If '
                 'they decide, it is possible to achieve a nuclear weapon-free '
                 'world within the lifetime of the Hibakusha.Turning its back '
                 'on this historic opportunity, the government of Japan has '
                 'clung to the “nuclear umbrella” of the U.S. and refused to '
                 'join this treaty. It is not only absolutely contrary to the '
                 'wishes of the Hibakusha and the people of the A-bombed '
                 'nation, but is a violation of the Constitution of Japan that '
                 'forever renounces all wars.The “Peace Wave” will start from '
                 'Japan at noon, September 20, and circle around the globe, '
                 'linking actions in different countries to call on all '
                 'governments of the world to join the treaty. In response to '
                 'the call by the World Conference against A and H Bombs, we '
                 'call on all of you to organize actions, setting the common '
                 'goal as “Abolition of nuclear weapons – Urging all '
                 'governments of the world to sign and ratify the Treaty on '
                 'the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons” and including the '
                 '“Hibakusha Appeal International Signature Campaign” as a '
                 'common action.In Japan, we will carry out:*At noon, '
                 'September 20, we will declare the start of “Peace Wave” in '
                 'Hiroshima, Nagasaki and Tokyo, and conduct a wide variety of '
                 'actions, including the street signature campaigns '
                 'nationwide.*Together with the Hibakusha, we will stage the '
                 '“Orizuru (peace crane) Action” from 1:30pm in front of the '
                 'Prime Minister’s Office, Tokyo to urge Prime Minister Abe '
                 'and the government of Japan to sign the Treaty. We will also '
                 'visit the embassies of nuclear weapon possessing countries '
                 'to call for their joining in the treaty.*We will continue to '
                 'carry out actions at various parts of Japan and on September '
                 '26, we will join a large scale of signature campaign to be '
                 'initiated by the Signature Campaign Promotion Committee.We '
                 'will call on all of you to join the “Peace Wave” actions to '
                 'circle the globe. Let us start planning/preparations for a '
                 'success of the starting actions and greater variety of '
                 'activities at your local communities, workplaces, school '
                 'campuses and all around the world.In many countries plans '
                 'are already being made to mark the occasion, and the '
                 'International Peace Bureau and other organizations are '
                 'promoting these actions in support of the “Peace '
                 'Wave.”Please send us your action plans to us. We will '
                 'translate them into Japanese language and spread them to the '
                 'Japanese movements, and instead, we will send out to you the '
                 'plans of Japan to link all actions in the world and '
                 'strengthen solidarity each other. We will appreciate very '
                 'much your disseminating this call in your networks and '
                 'links.',

                      '\\t</nav><!-- #nav-above -->\\n\\n\\t\\n<article '
                      'id="post-8212" class="content-single post-content '
                      'post-area post-author-id-7 shadow-custom rounded-all '
                      'font-inherit post-8212 post type-post status-publish '
                      'format-standard hentry category-calendar '
                      'category-en">\\n\\t\\t<header '
                      'class="page-header">\\n\\t\\t<h1 class="page-title '
                      'entry-title title-single '
                      'font-sans-serif"><small>2017/09/20-26</small><br>Build '
                      'the Peace Wave &amp; GENSUIKYO\\xe2\\x80\\x99S '
                      'CALL</h1>\\n\\t\\t<div class="entry-meta ">\\n<span '
                      'class="meta-info-wrap xxs-font-size '
                      'font-inherit">\\n<span class="sep posted-on">Posted on '
                      '</span><a '
                      'href="https://www.no-to-nato.org/2017/09/20170920-26build-the-peace-wave-gensuikyos-call/" '
                      'title="11:06 am" rel="bookmark"><time '
                      'class="entry-date" '
                      'datetime="2017-09-02T11:06:43+00:00">September 2, '
                      '2017</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span '
                      'class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a '
                      'class="url fn n" '
                      'href="https://www.no-to-nato.org/author/dus16/" '
                      'title="View all posts by tine" '
                      'rel="author">tine</a></span></span><span '
                      'class="updated">September 2, 2017</span>\\n</span><!-- '
                      '.entry-meta-icons --></div><!-- /entry-meta '
                      '-->\\n\\t</header><!-- .page-header -->\\n    <div '
                      'class="entry-content clearfix">\\n<h1>Help Build the '
                      'Peace '
                      'Wave</h1>\\n<h1>\\xe2\\x80\\x93\\xc2\\xa0September '
                      '20-26</h1>\\n<p>Dear Friends,</p>\\n<p>As many of you '
                      'will have seen, growing out of the World Conference '
                      'against A- &amp; H- Bombs in Hiroshima and Nagasaki, '
                      'Gensuikyo has initiated a call for a global '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d beginning '
                      'at\\xc2\\xa0noon\\xc2\\xa0on September 20, the day that '
                      'the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons will '
                      'be open for signatures at the United Nations. A number '
                      'of our European partner organizations have already '
                      'signed on.</p>\\n<p>Gensuikyo\\xe2\\x80\\x99s call, '
                      'which follows below, is for decentralized activities '
                      'consistent with the political cultures of each country '
                      'and the needs and methods or organizations committed to '
                      'nuclear weapons abolition.</p>\\n<p>After consultation, '
                      'Peace and Planet encourages member organizations and '
                      'all others to help build the Peace Wave. It is critical '
                      'that as many of the 122 governments that voted in favor '
                      'of the Treaty in July now sign and ratify it. We '
                      'believe that the most important Ban Treaty campaigning '
                      'will likely be in NATO and Asia-Pacific '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cnuclear umbrella\\xe2\\x80\\x9d states. '
                      'If just one or two governments break from their nuclear '
                      'masters, the foundations of the potentially omnicidal '
                      'nuclear disorder can be powerfully shaken.</p>\\n<p>For '
                      'those of us in nuclear weapons states, the Peace Wave '
                      'provides an opportunity to educate our movements and '
                      'communities about the Prohibition Treaty and to build '
                      'support for other nuclear disarmament initiatives, from '
                      'challenging the billions being spent to upgrade nuclear '
                      'arsenals and their delivery systems, to preventing '
                      'catastrophic wars with North Korea and '
                      'Iran.</p>\\n<p>Let\\xe2\\x80\\x99s build the Peace '
                      'Wave!</p>\\n<p>For Peace and Planet,</p>\\n<p>Joseph '
                      'Gerson</p>\\n<p>P.S. Please send notice of Peace Wave '
                      'events you have planned to\\xc2\\xa0<span '
                      'id="eeb-431718"></span><script '
                      'type="text/javascript">(function(){var '
                      'ml="a_mnhF2DiEtpsg%GbJlCAo-.3refk40c",mi=">HC0>6N4IJK>H7>66208B:E>HDA?JI<E3>MN0K<OGEI=>66>6N:0I=J:>H7>661@B03L>66>6NIJB>H7>663EE;J3JI>66>6NOB0<<>H7>66208B:EFB83L>66>H9A?JI<E3>MN0K<OGEI=>HC>650>H9",o="";for(var '
                      'j=0,l=mi.length;j<l;j++){o+=ml.charAt(mi.charCodeAt(j)-48);}document.getElementById("eeb-431718").innerHTML '
                      '= '
                      'decodeURIComponent(o);}());</script><noscript>*protected '
                      'email*</noscript></p>\\n<h3><b><u>GENSUIKYO\\xe2\\x80\\x99S '
                      'CALL</u></b></h3>\\n<p><b>Let Us Launch the '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d Actions '
                      'from\\xc2\\xa0September 20 to 26, calling on all '
                      'governments of the World to Join the Treaty to Prohibit '
                      'Nuclear Weapons</b></p>\\n<p>On the occasion of the '
                      '72nd anniversary of the atomic bombing of Hiroshima and '
                      'Nagasaki, the 2017 World Conference against A and H '
                      'Bombs called on the peoples of the world to launch '
                      'international join international simultaneous actions '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d to urge all '
                      'national governments to join the Treaty on the '
                      'Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons from September 20, the '
                      'day when the Treaty will be open for signatures, until '
                      '26, the International Day for the Total Elimination of '
                      'Nuclear Weapons.</p>\\n<p>The Treaty on the Prohibition '
                      'of Nuclear Weapons was adopted on\\xc2\\xa0July 7this '
                      'year with the support of 122 States. It is a '
                      'groundbreaking treaty to open a path to achieve the '
                      'total elimination of nuclear weapons, which has long '
                      'been aspired by the Hibakusha and the peoples of the '
                      'entire world. Declaring that nuclear weapons are '
                      'inhumane weapons in violation of international law, '
                      'international humanitarian law and international human '
                      'rights law, the treaty prohibits the development, '
                      'production, tests, manufacturing, acquisition, '
                      'possession, stockpiling, use and threat of use of '
                      'nuclear weapons.</p>\\n<p>Among the 193 member states '
                      'of the United Nations, only 9 countries are in '
                      'possession of nuclear weapons. If they decide, it is '
                      'possible to achieve a nuclear weapon-free world within '
                      'the lifetime of the Hibakusha.</p>\\n<p>Turning its '
                      'back on this historic opportunity, the government of '
                      'Japan has clung to the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cnuclear '
                      'umbrella\\xe2\\x80\\x9d of the U.S. and refused to join '
                      'this treaty. It is not only absolutely contrary to the '
                      'wishes of the Hibakusha and the people of the A-bombed '
                      'nation, but is a violation of the Constitution of Japan '
                      'that forever renounces all wars.</p>\\n<p>The '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d will start '
                      'from Japan at\\xc2\\xa0noon,\\xc2\\xa0September 20, and '
                      'circle around the globe, linking actions in different '
                      'countries to call on all governments of the world to '
                      'join the treaty. In response to the call by the World '
                      'Conference against A and H Bombs, we call on all of you '
                      'to organize actions, setting the common goal as '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cAbolition of nuclear weapons '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x93 Urging all governments of the world to '
                      'sign and ratify the Treaty on the Prohibition of '
                      'Nuclear Weapons\\xe2\\x80\\x9d and including the '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cHibakusha Appeal International Signature '
                      'Campaign\\xe2\\x80\\x9d as a common action.</p>\\n<p>In '
                      'Japan, we will carry '
                      'out:</p>\\n<p>*At\\xc2\\xa0noon,\\xc2\\xa0September 20, '
                      'we will declare the start of \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace '
                      'Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d in Hiroshima, Nagasaki and Tokyo, '
                      'and conduct a wide variety of actions, including the '
                      'street signature campaigns '
                      'nationwide.</p>\\n<p>*Together with the Hibakusha, we '
                      'will stage the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cOrizuru (peace crane) '
                      'Action\\xe2\\x80\\x9d from\\xc2\\xa01:30pm\\xc2\\xa0in '
                      'front of the Prime Minister\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Office, '
                      'Tokyo to urge Prime Minister Abe and the government of '
                      'Japan to sign the Treaty. We will also visit the '
                      'embassies of nuclear weapon possessing countries to '
                      'call for their joining in the treaty.</p>\\n<p>*We will '
                      'continue to carry out actions at various parts of Japan '
                      'and on\\xc2\\xa0September 26, we will join a large '
                      'scale of signature campaign to be initiated by the '
                      'Signature Campaign Promotion Committee.</p>\\n<p>Link '
                      'to the Hibakusha Appeal signature campaign:<a '
                      'href="https://click.everyaction.com/h/333121/2346543?&amp;hmac=jV9ue6zu_mkpXeBQtEOIeDUCG2npMlTuwkDzVJ0_DSA=&amp;id=132" '
                      'target="_blank" rel="noopener" '
                      'data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=https://click.everyaction.com/h/333121/2346543?&amp;hmac=jV9ue6zu_mkpXeBQtEOIeDUCG2npMlTuwkDzVJ0_DSA=?id%3D132&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1504226022846000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHw9C6ROlT8B22bsO7exXqXGaCaEg">http://www.antiatom.org/<wbr '
                      '/>english/our_activity/index.<wbr '
                      '/>php?id=132</a></p>\\n<p>We will call on all of you to '
                      'join the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d '
                      'actions to circle the globe. Let us start '
                      'planning/preparations for a success of the starting '
                      'actions and greater variety of activities at your local '
                      'communities, workplaces, school campuses and all around '
                      'the world.</p>\\n<p>In many countries plans are already '
                      'being made to mark the occasion, and the International '
                      'Peace Bureau and other organizations are promoting '
                      'these actions in support of the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace '
                      'Wave.\\xe2\\x80\\x9d</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n<p>Please '
                      'send us your action plans to us. We will translate them '
                      'into Japanese language and spread them to the Japanese '
                      'movements, and instead, we will send out to you the '
                      'plans of Japan to link all actions in the world and '
                      'strengthen solidarity each other. We will appreciate '
                      'very much your disseminating this call in your networks '
                      'and links.</p>\\n<p>Looking forward to working together '
                      'for \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace '
                      'Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d,</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n<p>Peace '
                      'Wave Task Force<br />\\nOrganizing Committee, the World '
                      'Conference against A and H Bombs<br />\\n2-4-4 Yushima, '
                      'Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo 113-8464 Japan<br '
                      '/>\\nEmail:\\xc2\\xa0<span '

                 'with the political cultures of each country and the needs '
                 'and methods or organizations committed to nuclear weapons '

                 'omnicidal nuclear disorder can be powerfully shaken.For '

                 'Nuclear WeaponsOn the occasion of the 72nd anniversary of '
                 'the atomic bombing of Hiroshima and Nagasaki, the 2017 World '
                 'Conference against A and H Bombs called on the peoples of '
                 'the world to launch international join international '
                 'simultaneous actions “Peace Wave” to urge all national '
                 'governments to join the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear '
                 'Weapons from September 20, the day when the Treaty will be '
                 'open for signatures, until 26, the International Day for the '
                 'Total Elimination of Nuclear Weapons.The Treaty on the '
                 'Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons was adopted on July 7this '
                 'year with the support of 122 States. It is a groundbreaking '
                 'treaty to open a path to achieve the total elimination of '
                 'nuclear weapons, which has long been aspired by the '
                 'Hibakusha and the peoples of the entire world. Declaring '
                 'that nuclear weapons are inhumane weapons in violation of '
                 'international law, international humanitarian law and '
                 'international human rights law, the treaty prohibits the '
                 'development, production, tests, manufacturing, acquisition, '
                 'possession, stockpiling, use and threat of use of nuclear '
                 'weapons.Among the 193 member states of the United Nations, '
                 'only 9 countries are in possession of nuclear weapons. If '
                 'they decide, it is possible to achieve a nuclear weapon-free '
                 'world within the lifetime of the Hibakusha.Turning its back '
                 'on this historic opportunity, the government of Japan has '
                 'clung to the “nuclear umbrella” of the U.S. and refused to '
                 'join this treaty. It is not only absolutely contrary to the '
                 'wishes of the Hibakusha and the people of the A-bombed '
                 'nation, but is a violation of the Constitution of Japan that '
                 'forever renounces all wars.The “Peace Wave” will start from '
                 'Japan at noon, September 20, and circle around the globe, '
                 'linking actions in different countries to call on all '
                 'governments of the world to join the treaty. In response to '
                 'the call by the World Conference against A and H Bombs, we '
                 'call on all of you to organize actions, setting the common '
                 'goal as “Abolition of nuclear weapons – Urging all '
                 'governments of the world to sign and ratify the Treaty on '
                 'the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons” and including the '
                 '“Hibakusha Appeal International Signature Campaign” as a '
                 'common action.In Japan, we will carry out:*At noon, '
                 'September 20, we will declare the start of “Peace Wave” in '

                 'actions, including the street signature campaigns '

                 'Prime Minister’s Office, Tokyo to urge Prime Minister Abe '

                      'id="post-8212" class="content-single post-content '
                      'post-area post-author-id-7 shadow-custom rounded-all '
                      'font-inherit post-8212 post type-post status-publish '
                      'format-standard hentry category-calendar '
                      'category-en">\\n\\t\\t<header '
                      'class="page-header">\\n\\t\\t<h1 class="page-title '
                      'entry-title title-single '
                      'font-sans-serif"><small>2017/09/20-26</small><br>Build '
                      'the Peace Wave &amp; GENSUIKYO\\xe2\\x80\\x99S '
                      'CALL</h1>\\n\\t\\t<div class="entry-meta ">\\n<span '
                      'class="meta-info-wrap xxs-font-size '
                      'font-inherit">\\n<span class="sep posted-on">Posted on '
                      '</span><a '
                      'href="https://www.no-to-nato.org/2017/09/20170920-26build-the-peace-wave-gensuikyos-call/" '
                      'title="11:06 am" rel="bookmark"><time '
                      'class="entry-date" '
                      'datetime="2017-09-02T11:06:43+00:00">September 2, '
                      '2017</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span '
                      'class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a '
                      'class="url fn n" '
                      'href="https://www.no-to-nato.org/author/dus16/" '
                      'title="View all posts by tine" '
                      'rel="author">tine</a></span></span><span '
                      'class="updated">September 2, 2017</span>\\n</span><!-- '
                      '.entry-meta-icons --></div><!-- /entry-meta '
                      '-->\\n\\t</header><!-- .page-header -->\\n    <div '
                      'class="entry-content clearfix">\\n<h1>Help Build the '
                      'Peace '
                      'Wave</h1>\\n<h1>\\xe2\\x80\\x93\\xc2\\xa0September '
                      '20-26</h1>\\n<p>Dear Friends,</p>\\n<p>As many of you '
                      'will have seen, growing out of the World Conference '
                      'against A- &amp; H- Bombs in Hiroshima and Nagasaki, '
                      'Gensuikyo has initiated a call for a global '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d beginning '
                      'at\\xc2\\xa0noon\\xc2\\xa0on September 20, the day that '
                      'the Treaty on the Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons will '
                      'be open for signatures at the United Nations. A number '
                      'of our European partner organizations have already '
                      'signed on.</p>\\n<p>Gensuikyo\\xe2\\x80\\x99s call, '
                      'which follows below, is for decentralized activities '
                      'consistent with the political cultures of each country '
                      'and the needs and methods or organizations committed to '
                      'nuclear weapons abolition.</p>\\n<p>After consultation, '
                      'Peace and Planet encourages member organizations and '
                      'all others to help build the Peace Wave. It is critical '
                      'that as many of the 122 governments that voted in favor '
                      'of the Treaty in July now sign and ratify it. We '
                      'believe that the most important Ban Treaty campaigning '
                      'will likely be in NATO and Asia-Pacific '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cnuclear umbrella\\xe2\\x80\\x9d states. '
                      'If just one or two governments break from their nuclear '
                      'masters, the foundations of the potentially omnicidal '
                      'nuclear disorder can be powerfully shaken.</p>\\n<p>For '
                      'those of us in nuclear weapons states, the Peace Wave '
                      'provides an opportunity to educate our movements and '
                      'communities about the Prohibition Treaty and to build '
                      'support for other nuclear disarmament initiatives, from '
                      'challenging the billions being spent to upgrade nuclear '
                      'arsenals and their delivery systems, to preventing '
                      'catastrophic wars with North Korea and '
                      'Iran.</p>\\n<p>Let\\xe2\\x80\\x99s build the Peace '
                      'Wave!</p>\\n<p>For Peace and Planet,</p>\\n<p>Joseph '
                      'Gerson</p>\\n<p>P.S. Please send notice of Peace Wave '
                      'events you have planned to\\xc2\\xa0<span '
                      'id="eeb-85857"></span><script '
                      'type="text/javascript">(function(){var '
                      'ml="3t0Clkg_G2arsD.fm4-pF%JhnEobeiAc",mi="E03:E92G;L?E0=E99@:M41JE0NF8L;<JHEA2:?<O>J;6E99E921:;6L1E0=E997K4:H5E99E92;L4E0=E99HJJCLHL;E99E92O4:<<E0=E99@:M41JB4MH5E99E0IF8L;<JHEA2:?<O>J;6E03E9D:E0I",o="";for(var '
                      'j=0,l=mi.length;j<l;j++){o+=ml.charAt(mi.charCodeAt(j)-48);}document.getElementById("eeb-85857").innerHTML '
                      '= '
                      'decodeURIComponent(o);}());</script><noscript>*protected '
                      'email*</noscript></p>\\n<h3><b><u>GENSUIKYO\\xe2\\x80\\x99S '
                      'CALL</u></b></h3>\\n<p><b>Let Us Launch the '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d Actions '
                      'from\\xc2\\xa0September 20 to 26, calling on all '
                      'governments of the World to Join the Treaty to Prohibit '
                      'Nuclear Weapons</b></p>\\n<p>On the occasion of the '
                      '72nd anniversary of the atomic bombing of Hiroshima and '
                      'Nagasaki, the 2017 World Conference against A and H '
                      'Bombs called on the peoples of the world to launch '
                      'international join international simultaneous actions '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d to urge all '
                      'national governments to join the Treaty on the '
                      'Prohibition of Nuclear Weapons from September 20, the '
                      'day when the Treaty will be open for signatures, until '
                      '26, the International Day for the Total Elimination of '
                      'Nuclear Weapons.</p>\\n<p>The Treaty on the Prohibition '
                      'of Nuclear Weapons was adopted on\\xc2\\xa0July 7this '
                      'year with the support of 122 States. It is a '
                      'groundbreaking treaty to open a path to achieve the '
                      'total elimination of nuclear weapons, which has long '
                      'been aspired by the Hibakusha and the peoples of the '
                      'entire world. Declaring that nuclear weapons are '
                      'inhumane weapons in violation of international law, '
                      'international humanitarian law and international human '
                      'rights law, the treaty prohibits the development, '
                      'production, tests, manufacturing, acquisition, '
                      'possession, stockpiling, use and threat of use of '
                      'nuclear weapons.</p>\\n<p>Among the 193 member states '
                      'of the United Nations, only 9 countries are in '
                      'possession of nuclear weapons. If they decide, it is '
                      'possible to achieve a nuclear weapon-free world within '
                      'the lifetime of the Hibakusha.</p>\\n<p>Turning its '
                      'back on this historic opportunity, the government of '
                      'Japan has clung to the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cnuclear '
                      'umbrella\\xe2\\x80\\x9d of the U.S. and refused to join '
                      'this treaty. It is not only absolutely contrary to the '
                      'wishes of the Hibakusha and the people of the A-bombed '
                      'nation, but is a violation of the Constitution of Japan '
                      'that forever renounces all wars.</p>\\n<p>The '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d will start '
                      'from Japan at\\xc2\\xa0noon,\\xc2\\xa0September 20, and '
                      'circle around the globe, linking actions in different '
                      'countries to call on all governments of the world to '
                      'join the treaty. In response to the call by the World '
                      'Conference against A and H Bombs, we call on all of you '
                      'to organize actions, setting the common goal as '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cAbolition of nuclear weapons '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x93 Urging all governments of the world to '
                      'sign and ratify the Treaty on the Prohibition of '
                      'Nuclear Weapons\\xe2\\x80\\x9d and including the '
                      '\\xe2\\x80\\x9cHibakusha Appeal International Signature '
                      'Campaign\\xe2\\x80\\x9d as a common action.</p>\\n<p>In '
                      'Japan, we will carry '
                      'out:</p>\\n<p>*At\\xc2\\xa0noon,\\xc2\\xa0September 20, '
                      'we will declare the start of \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace '
                      'Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d in Hiroshima, Nagasaki and Tokyo, '
                      'and conduct a wide variety of actions, including the '
                      'street signature campaigns '
                      'nationwide.</p>\\n<p>*Together with the Hibakusha, we '
                      'will stage the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cOrizuru (peace crane) '
                      'Action\\xe2\\x80\\x9d from\\xc2\\xa01:30pm\\xc2\\xa0in '
                      'front of the Prime Minister\\xe2\\x80\\x99s Office, '
                      'Tokyo to urge Prime Minister Abe and the government of '
                      'Japan to sign the Treaty. We will also visit the '
                      'embassies of nuclear weapon possessing countries to '
                      'call for their joining in the treaty.</p>\\n<p>*We will '
                      'continue to carry out actions at various parts of Japan '
                      'and on\\xc2\\xa0September 26, we will join a large '
                      'scale of signature campaign to be initiated by the '
                      'Signature Campaign Promotion Committee.</p>\\n<p>Link '
                      'to the Hibakusha Appeal signature campaign:<a '
                      'href="https://click.everyaction.com/h/333121/2346543?&amp;hmac=jV9ue6zu_mkpXeBQtEOIeDUCG2npMlTuwkDzVJ0_DSA=&amp;id=132" '
                      'target="_blank" rel="noopener" '
                      'data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=https://click.everyaction.com/h/333121/2346543?&amp;hmac=jV9ue6zu_mkpXeBQtEOIeDUCG2npMlTuwkDzVJ0_DSA=?id%3D132&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1504226022846000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHw9C6ROlT8B22bsO7exXqXGaCaEg">http://www.antiatom.org/<wbr '
                      '/>english/our_activity/index.<wbr '
                      '/>php?id=132</a></p>\\n<p>We will call on all of you to '
                      'join the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d '
                      'actions to circle the globe. Let us start '
                      'planning/preparations for a success of the starting '
                      'actions and greater variety of activities at your local '
                      'communities, workplaces, school campuses and all around '
                      'the world.</p>\\n<p>In many countries plans are already '
                      'being made to mark the occasion, and the International '
                      'Peace Bureau and other organizations are promoting '
                      'these actions in support of the \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace '
                      'Wave.\\xe2\\x80\\x9d</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n<p>Please '
                      'send us your action plans to us. We will translate them '
                      'into Japanese language and spread them to the Japanese '
                      'movements, and instead, we will send out to you the '
                      'plans of Japan to link all actions in the world and '
                      'strengthen solidarity each other. We will appreciate '
                      'very much your disseminating this call in your networks '
                      'and links.</p>\\n<p>Looking forward to working together '
                      'for \\xe2\\x80\\x9cPeace '
                      'Wave\\xe2\\x80\\x9d,</p>\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\n<p>Peace '
                      'Wave Task Force<br />\\nOrganizing Committee, the World '
                      'Conference against A and H Bombs<br />\\n2-4-4 Yushima, '
                      'Bunkyo-ku, Tokyo 113-8464 Japan<br '
                      '/>\\nEmail:\\xc2\\xa0<span '
                      'id="eeb-516065"></span><script '
                      'type="text/javascript">(function(){var '
                      'ml="hAC0Dabcl.j4r3ztf_mF2g-e%nspkEoi",mi="H=25HD30<G@H=4HDDB5O8?NH=15I?O5?NBH;3?NK5>9K85859N<9:KHDDHD3?5<EG?H=4HDDA685ILHDDHD3<G8H=4HDDINNKGIG<HDDHD3785JJH=4HDDB5O8?NF8OILHDDH=M5I?O5?NBH;3?NK5>9K85859N<9:KH=2HDC5H=M",o="";for(var '
